1
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:39,999
=The Litchi Road=

2
00:01:40,940 --> 00:01:42,420
I didn't pick you up yesterday.

3
00:01:42,830 --> 00:01:44,020
Don't be mad at me.

4
00:01:44,977 --> 00:01:47,333
(Coworkers' "Love")
Something happened at Leyou Garden.

5
00:01:47,830 --> 00:01:49,940
Someone ruined His Majesty's

6
00:01:50,380 --> 00:01:51,755
favorite peonies.

7
00:01:55,020 --> 00:01:56,220
If His Majesty

8
00:01:56,220 --> 00:01:57,470
blames us,

9
00:01:57,470 --> 00:01:58,500
my colleagues

10
00:01:58,500 --> 00:01:59,711
will all lose their heads.

11
00:02:00,020 --> 00:02:01,500
They're terrified

12
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:03,110
and can only ask me for help.

13
00:02:03,644 --> 00:02:05,888
Why are you
the only one who can save them?

14
00:02:06,660 --> 00:02:07,830
You saw me

15
00:02:07,830 --> 00:02:09,220
tending to plants.

16
00:02:09,660 --> 00:02:11,590
No one in Shanglin Office can rival me.

17
00:02:12,220 --> 00:02:13,100
I'm the best

18
00:02:13,100 --> 00:02:14,150
in Leyou Garden.

19
00:02:14,700 --> 00:02:15,540
So

20
00:02:15,910 --> 00:02:18,630
if I went to save the peonies,

21
00:02:18,688 --> 00:02:20,149
I couldn't come to pick you up.

22
00:02:20,150 --> 00:02:21,220
If I don't save the peonies,

23
00:02:21,220 --> 00:02:22,844
my colleagues will lose their heads.

24
00:02:23,070 --> 00:02:24,380
Should I save them or not?

25
00:02:26,750 --> 00:02:28,244
Did you save the peonies?

26
00:02:29,380 --> 00:02:30,500
If I take action,

27
00:02:30,750 --> 00:02:32,100
I can solve it easily.

28
00:02:33,940 --> 00:02:35,470
You saved your colleagues.

29
00:02:35,780 --> 00:02:37,470
They must be very grateful.

30
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:40,340
Of course.

31
00:02:43,700 --> 00:02:45,150
I saved their lives.

32
00:02:46,470 --> 00:02:48,111
They're especially grateful.

33
00:02:56,860 --> 00:02:59,860
=Episode 3=

34
00:03:01,140 --> 00:03:06,540
(March, 13th Year of Tianbao,
Lingnan, Gaozhou)

35
00:03:19,977 --> 00:03:21,288
Gou'er, do you feel hot?

36
00:03:22,100 --> 00:03:22,940
Yes.

37
00:03:23,430 --> 00:03:24,430
Why is it so hot?

38
00:03:25,150 --> 00:03:26,820
Let's go buy a fan someday.

39
00:03:29,980 --> 00:03:31,870
We haven't been here before.
It's so hot here.

40
00:03:39,070 --> 00:03:40,630
Do you remember what I taught you?

41
00:03:40,630 --> 00:03:41,470
Yes.

42
00:03:45,577 --> 00:03:46,620
What are you here for?

43
00:03:46,980 --> 00:03:47,820
You slave.

44
00:03:48,220 --> 00:03:49,070
You're blind.

45
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:50,870
Look who's here.

46
00:03:51,540 --> 00:03:52,780
Why did you hit a servant?

47
00:03:53,820 --> 00:03:54,660
Yes.

48
00:03:54,666 --> 00:03:56,030
How dare you call others a slave?

49
00:03:57,310 --> 00:03:58,150
How insolent.

50
00:03:59,150 --> 00:04:00,266
Why are you standing there?

51
00:04:00,430 --> 00:04:01,430
Hurry and lead the way.

52
00:04:03,070 --> 00:04:03,980
Your Excellency.

53
00:04:03,980 --> 00:04:04,820
This way, please.

54
00:04:23,180 --> 00:04:26,140
(Zhao Xinmin,
Chief Scribe of Inspector's Office)

55
00:04:28,020 --> 00:04:30,155
You're not eating it right.

56
00:04:31,110 --> 00:04:33,140
Sugar cane can't be eaten directly.

57
00:04:33,990 --> 00:04:36,266
You need to chew it and suck the juice.

58
00:04:39,110 --> 00:04:40,580
Then, spit out the residue.

59
00:04:46,820 --> 00:04:48,820
Judging from your temperament,

60
00:04:49,430 --> 00:04:52,190
you must be Inspector He.

61
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:53,340
I dare not.

62
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:55,820
I'm Inspector He's chief scribe.

63
00:04:56,340 --> 00:04:58,190
I'm Zhao Xin,
and my courtesy name is Xinmin.

64
00:04:58,670 --> 00:04:59,750
May I ask who you are?

65
00:05:00,940 --> 00:05:02,190
I'm Ma Guiyun.

66
00:05:02,580 --> 00:05:04,020
Right Chancellor's subordinate.

67
00:05:04,500 --> 00:05:06,190
You seem older.

68
00:05:06,190 --> 00:05:09,260
Is it appropriate to call you Xinmin?

69
00:05:09,260 --> 00:05:10,310
No.

70
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:11,820
I think it's very inappropriate.

71
00:05:24,870 --> 00:05:27,070
You're Right Chancellor's favorite.

72
00:05:27,070 --> 00:05:28,820
I'm just a minor official in Lingnan.

73
00:05:29,110 --> 00:05:30,260
I should call you

74
00:05:30,990 --> 00:05:31,870
Guiyun.

75
00:05:33,990 --> 00:05:35,740
We can call each other whatever we want.

76
00:05:37,260 --> 00:05:38,260
Before leaving,

77
00:05:38,260 --> 00:05:39,940
Pan Bao gave me a token.

78
00:05:40,260 --> 00:05:41,940
See

79
00:05:44,133 --> 00:05:45,340
if you recognize it.

80
00:06:02,110 --> 00:06:03,260
Xinmin, look carefully.

81
00:06:04,670 --> 00:06:05,510
Look slowly.

82
00:06:07,340 --> 00:06:08,340
Guiyun, don't blame me.

83
00:06:08,340 --> 00:06:09,690
It's not that I don't believe you.

84
00:06:09,990 --> 00:06:11,790
It's just that this jade can't speak.

85
00:06:12,380 --> 00:06:14,230
I have an agreement with Pan Bao.

86
00:06:14,870 --> 00:06:16,020
If he gave it away willingly,

87
00:06:16,260 --> 00:06:18,120
he'll secretly chip off

88
00:06:18,940 --> 00:06:19,900
a corner of the token

89
00:06:19,900 --> 00:06:20,790
to prevent...

90
00:06:21,700 --> 00:06:22,870
Guiyun, do you understand?

91
00:06:23,990 --> 00:06:24,830
Yes.

92
00:06:25,990 --> 00:06:27,990
You're really cautious.

93
00:06:29,630 --> 00:06:30,790
Is the corner

94
00:06:32,790 --> 00:06:33,700
chipped off?

95
00:06:44,550 --> 00:06:45,500
Yes.

96
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:46,670
It's indeed chipped off.

97
00:06:47,230 --> 00:06:48,230
It's genuine.

98
00:06:50,110 --> 00:06:51,380
But why didn't Pan Bao

99
00:06:51,380 --> 00:06:52,580
come back with you

100
00:06:52,580 --> 00:06:53,820
and ask you

101
00:06:53,820 --> 00:06:54,870
to come here?

102
00:06:56,430 --> 00:06:57,580
Right Chancellor said

103
00:06:58,020 --> 00:07:00,070
Inspector He's matter is a big deal.

104
00:07:00,070 --> 00:07:01,133
No mistakes are allowed.

105
00:07:01,230 --> 00:07:02,500
He gave me the token

106
00:07:02,820 --> 00:07:04,380
and asked me to come to Lingnan

107
00:07:04,990 --> 00:07:06,790
and meet Inspector He first.

108
00:07:11,940 --> 00:07:13,920
I've never met Right Chancellor.

109
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:15,190
Meeting you today

110
00:07:15,940 --> 00:07:18,230
is like meeting Right Chancellor.

111
00:07:19,380 --> 00:07:20,630
Where's Pan Bao?

112
00:07:20,822 --> 00:07:22,666
Pan Bao
is of course with Right Chancellor.

113
00:07:22,700 --> 00:07:23,790
He handed me the token

114
00:07:24,244 --> 00:07:25,340
and let me bring it over.

115
00:07:26,190 --> 00:07:27,580
Xinmin, don't you understand?

116
00:07:31,380 --> 00:07:32,220
I see.

117
00:07:33,940 --> 00:07:34,790
I've been foolish.

118
00:07:35,070 --> 00:07:36,020
For such a big matter,

119
00:07:36,020 --> 00:07:37,670
it would be good for both sides

120
00:07:37,670 --> 00:07:39,088
to have someone to liaise with.

121
00:07:40,070 --> 00:07:40,910
Well.

122
00:07:41,260 --> 00:07:42,100
Did Right Chancellor

123
00:07:43,020 --> 00:07:44,340
give you any other items

124
00:07:44,820 --> 00:07:45,870
to bring over?

125
00:07:46,430 --> 00:07:47,270
There's

126
00:07:48,260 --> 00:07:49,340
indeed one thing.

127
00:08:01,310 --> 00:08:03,460
Right Chancellor solemnly instructed me

128
00:08:03,460 --> 00:08:05,260
to personally hand this item

129
00:08:05,260 --> 00:08:06,750
over to Inspector He.

130
00:08:07,230 --> 00:08:08,630
I must not hand it over to others.

131
00:08:08,630 --> 00:08:09,470
Otherwise,

132
00:08:09,750 --> 00:08:12,070
I didn't have to travel so far
to get here.

133
00:08:15,670 --> 00:08:16,510
I see.

134
00:08:19,020 --> 00:08:20,140
But Inspector He

135
00:08:21,580 --> 00:08:22,790
went out patrolling

136
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:24,022
and hasn't come back yet.

137
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:26,630
Why don't you

138
00:08:26,900 --> 00:08:27,740
rest for a few days

139
00:08:28,020 --> 00:08:28,860
and let me

140
00:08:29,110 --> 00:08:30,550
host you?

141
00:08:31,870 --> 00:08:32,860
In that case,

142
00:08:32,860 --> 00:08:34,422
Right Chancellor has one more thing

143
00:08:34,422 --> 00:08:35,466
that needs you

144
00:08:35,510 --> 00:08:37,190
to report to Inspector He in advance.

145
00:08:39,460 --> 00:08:40,980
I will obey Right Chancellor's orders.

146
00:08:41,790 --> 00:08:44,620
Does he want gold and silver or...

147
00:08:45,670 --> 00:08:46,550
South Sea treasures?

148
00:08:47,790 --> 00:08:48,630
Neither.

149
00:08:49,220 --> 00:08:50,430
It's a letter.

150
00:08:54,940 --> 00:08:57,190
If Inspector He could personally

151
00:08:57,190 --> 00:08:58,866
write a letter of allegiance

152
00:08:59,270 --> 00:09:00,220
to Right Chancellor,

153
00:09:01,390 --> 00:09:02,510
we'll have no doubts

154
00:09:02,510 --> 00:09:03,350
about each other

155
00:09:04,150 --> 00:09:05,460
and cooperate sincerely.

156
00:09:08,220 --> 00:09:10,150
Is this letter of allegiance

157
00:09:10,150 --> 00:09:12,030
for the court or for Right Chancellor?

158
00:09:14,510 --> 00:09:17,310
Inspector He's loyalty to His Majesty

159
00:09:18,340 --> 00:09:20,030
is obvious to all.

160
00:09:20,390 --> 00:09:21,700
Does Right Chancellor

161
00:09:22,660 --> 00:09:23,980
still have doubts

162
00:09:24,088 --> 00:09:25,644
about Inspector He's sincerity?

163
00:09:25,900 --> 00:09:26,740
How about this?

164
00:09:27,140 --> 00:09:28,220
Let me tell you a story

165
00:09:28,980 --> 00:09:30,420
about the Chang'an banquet.

166
00:09:32,460 --> 00:09:33,340
An official

167
00:09:33,940 --> 00:09:35,820
needed to do something confidential.

168
00:09:36,260 --> 00:09:37,340
He had two subordinates.

169
00:09:37,533 --> 00:09:39,140
One has made meritorious achievements

170
00:09:39,140 --> 00:09:40,822
while another has committed a crime.

171
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:43,088
How would you choose?

172
00:09:43,111 --> 00:09:44,770
I'll choose
the one who committed a crime.

173
00:09:44,770 --> 00:09:46,666
With evidence in my hand,
I can order him around.

174
00:09:49,060 --> 00:09:50,100
I see.

175
00:09:50,733 --> 00:09:52,100
As a low-ranking subordinate,

176
00:09:52,100 --> 00:09:54,266
I'm not worthy to know
what's on the higher-ups' minds.

177
00:09:54,311 --> 00:09:55,940
Right Chancellor has given instructions.

178
00:09:56,740 --> 00:09:57,580
A letter

179
00:09:58,540 --> 00:09:59,580
in exchange for a tally.

180
00:10:01,340 --> 00:10:02,180
(It is said)

181
00:10:02,580 --> 00:10:04,260
(that He Youguang)

182
00:10:04,260 --> 00:10:06,340
(experienced a disaster at sea
many years ago.)

183
00:10:07,060 --> 00:10:09,420
(He was like an immortal evil spirit,)

184
00:10:09,420 --> 00:10:11,820
(slaughtering in the blazing flames.)

185
00:10:11,820 --> 00:10:13,700
(Fighting Bird)
(In the next decade,)

186
00:10:13,700 --> 00:10:15,180
(he occupied Lingnan,)

187
00:10:15,180 --> 00:10:16,340
(holding absolute power.)

188
00:10:16,820 --> 00:10:19,540
(He Youguang, Gaozhou's Inspector)

189
00:10:23,020 --> 00:10:24,060
Good news.

190
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:25,620
Good news.

191
00:10:25,620 --> 00:10:26,740
Give it to me.

192
00:10:26,740 --> 00:10:27,911
He didn't give it right away.

193
00:10:27,911 --> 00:10:29,060
He said he had to personally

194
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:30,380
hand it to you.

195
00:10:30,888 --> 00:10:32,340
Why didn't you say that earlier?

196
00:10:32,340 --> 00:10:33,220
I'll get it myself.

197
00:10:33,220 --> 00:10:34,500
Calm down.

198
00:10:34,740 --> 00:10:35,620
He made a request.

199
00:10:35,980 --> 00:10:36,820
What request?

200
00:10:37,580 --> 00:10:38,420
Right Chancellor

201
00:10:38,780 --> 00:10:39,780
wants you

202
00:10:39,780 --> 00:10:41,100
to write a letter of allegiance.

203
00:10:41,740 --> 00:10:42,620
Write it then.

204
00:10:43,420 --> 00:10:44,580
Don't say that.

205
00:10:46,980 --> 00:10:47,820
This letter

206
00:10:48,300 --> 00:10:49,860
isn't for His Majesty

207
00:10:49,860 --> 00:10:51,300
but Right Chancellor.

208
00:10:52,420 --> 00:10:53,340
You'll give others

209
00:10:53,340 --> 00:10:55,180
solid leverage over you.

210
00:10:55,180 --> 00:10:57,380
If someone sees this letter, then...

211
00:10:57,380 --> 00:10:58,660
Then what?

212
00:10:59,180 --> 00:11:01,100
Isn't it obvious?

213
00:11:01,100 --> 00:11:02,300
We're indeed in collusion

214
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:03,340
with Right Chancellor.

215
00:11:03,340 --> 00:11:04,380
That's different.

216
00:11:04,488 --> 00:11:05,540
What's the difference?

217
00:11:06,620 --> 00:11:07,740
His Majesty can tolerate

218
00:11:08,177 --> 00:11:09,688
two ministers colluding.

219
00:11:10,220 --> 00:11:12,260
One minister being loyal to another

220
00:11:12,660 --> 00:11:14,180
instead of His Majesty

221
00:11:14,180 --> 00:11:16,060
is a big problem.

222
00:11:17,140 --> 00:11:18,700
Right Chancellor is calculating.

223
00:11:18,940 --> 00:11:19,820
I think this matter

224
00:11:19,820 --> 00:11:20,860
isn't that simple.

225
00:11:20,860 --> 00:11:21,890
It's not that complicated.

226
00:11:21,890 --> 00:11:22,733
It's not that simple.

227
00:11:22,830 --> 00:11:24,030
It's not that complicated.

228
00:11:25,670 --> 00:11:27,060
To put it bluntly, this letter

229
00:11:27,060 --> 00:11:28,460
is just a token of allegiance.

230
00:11:29,260 --> 00:11:31,460
After you give this letter to him,

231
00:11:31,820 --> 00:11:33,020
he'll feel at ease.

232
00:11:33,560 --> 00:11:34,620
When he feels at ease,

233
00:11:34,620 --> 00:11:35,666
I will also feel at ease.

234
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:36,860
We'll both feel at ease.

235
00:11:36,860 --> 00:11:37,820
We're all at ease now.

236
00:11:37,820 --> 00:11:38,780
We can't be at ease.

237
00:11:39,100 --> 00:11:41,260
He's using this military tally

238
00:11:41,260 --> 00:11:42,100
to threaten us.

239
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:43,740
I think he's fishing.

240
00:11:43,740 --> 00:11:44,980
What is he fishing for?

241
00:11:44,980 --> 00:11:45,820
I've made up my mind.

242
00:11:46,620 --> 00:11:47,700
Arrange it tonight.

243
00:11:48,260 --> 00:11:49,180
Give him the letter.

244
00:11:49,620 --> 00:11:51,100
Bring back the military tally.

245
00:11:51,380 --> 00:11:52,860
All the things we sent

246
00:11:52,860 --> 00:11:53,700
can't go to waste.

247
00:12:01,820 --> 00:12:02,780
You're wise.

248
00:12:02,780 --> 00:12:03,660
I worry too much.

249
00:12:04,100 --> 00:12:05,180
Tonight, this military tally

250
00:12:05,180 --> 00:12:07,180
will be yours tonight.

251
00:12:09,222 --> 00:12:10,500
That's the right attitude.

252
00:12:10,900 --> 00:12:11,740
Let me tell you.

253
00:12:11,740 --> 00:12:13,500
Once we get the military tally,

254
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:15,260
I'll replace

255
00:12:15,260 --> 00:12:15,980
everyone

256
00:12:15,980 --> 00:12:17,060
within three months.

257
00:12:17,340 --> 00:12:18,380
Who in Lingnan

258
00:12:18,660 --> 00:12:19,940
can possibly stand against us?

259
00:12:19,940 --> 00:12:20,620
Yes.

260
00:12:20,620 --> 00:12:21,660
With your methods,

261
00:12:21,660 --> 00:12:23,860
Lingnan should be called Hezhou

262
00:12:23,860 --> 00:12:24,700
by then.

263
00:13:12,980 --> 00:13:13,820
Sir.

264
00:13:15,660 --> 00:13:18,220
Is Inspector's Office this way?

265
00:13:52,020 --> 00:13:57,140
(The 3rd day of February, 13th year
of Tianbao: Dispatch the Litchi Envoy)

266
00:13:59,740 --> 00:14:02,300
(Inspector's Office)

267
00:14:10,100 --> 00:14:10,940
Stop.

268
00:14:10,940 --> 00:14:13,780
(Inspector's Office)

269
00:14:13,780 --> 00:14:14,620
Who are you?

270
00:14:15,900 --> 00:14:20,020
I'm the Litchi Envoy
appointed by the imperial court.

271
00:14:20,620 --> 00:14:22,220
I'm here to see Inspector He.

272
00:14:48,380 --> 00:14:49,220
Zhao.

273
00:14:50,140 --> 00:14:51,260
Who

274
00:14:51,260 --> 00:14:52,300
was the last envoy?

275
00:14:52,300 --> 00:14:53,140
Coconut Envoy.

276
00:14:53,380 --> 00:14:54,220
Coconut Envoy

277
00:14:55,340 --> 00:14:56,260
came here

278
00:14:56,260 --> 00:14:57,540
and fooled us.

279
00:14:58,020 --> 00:14:59,020
Right?

280
00:14:59,020 --> 00:15:01,220
The envoy this time is...

281
00:15:01,420 --> 00:15:03,340
I'm Litchi Envoy.

282
00:15:04,380 --> 00:15:05,220
Litchi Envoy?

283
00:15:06,540 --> 00:15:07,660
What does Litchi Envoy do?

284
00:15:15,540 --> 00:15:16,380
I...

285
00:15:17,220 --> 00:15:18,380
I was ordered by His Majesty

286
00:15:18,820 --> 00:15:20,500
to get fresh litchis.

287
00:15:21,066 --> 00:15:23,066
It's all written
in the appointment decree.

288
00:15:23,540 --> 00:15:24,580
Please

289
00:15:24,580 --> 00:15:26,980
provide me with assistance.

290
00:15:32,940 --> 00:15:33,980
To be honest,

291
00:15:33,980 --> 00:15:34,820
it's well done.

292
00:15:35,460 --> 00:15:36,300
Exquisite.

293
